49
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:22,320
system where you answer quizzes and repeat patterns until the penny drops and you eventually

50
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:26,800
get it. Generally, when you teach people a second language, you actually show them the

51
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:31,440
grammatical structures first before jumping into examples and tests so that the learner

52
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:35,440
doesn't have to magically figure it out through trial and error. If you really want to pick

53
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:39,440
up a second language, taking a proper course or studying in a more traditional way with

