64
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:48,880
If you were ever a child who had recess, you're probably familiar with this language game.

65
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:54,080
It involves transforming words by moving the first consonant to the end and adding a.

66
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:57,520
The goal is usually to be able to speak in a kind of code language.

67
00:05:57,520 --> 00:06:02,320
Adults supposedly can't understand it, so it's kids only. No adults allowed.

68
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:07,200
Unbeknownst to the kids, those adults probably did the exact same thing when they were younger,

69
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:11,200
and can understand absolutely everything they say. Time is a flat circle.

70
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:16,160
Here's an example. Like and subscribe would turn into eichle, andier,

71
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:21,360
obscribesay. Funnily enough, this fake language actually follows some structural rules.

72
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:26,960
The easiest words to translate start with consonant sounds. Coffee becomes offy-k.

73
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:31,360
