121
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,120
like learning a second language for work,

122
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,840
soldiers who might have learned some Arabic while abroad,

123
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,760
or even duolingo users.

124
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:29,200
The European Commission Census from 2006 had a 56% multilingual rate,

125
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,880
but their question was,

126
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:34,480
can you have a conversation in a language besides your mother tongue,

127
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:36,320
which is quite a bit more broad.

128
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,080
So purely based on this data,

129
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:42,240
we can't say for sure if Americans really are more likely to be monolingual

130
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,280
than the rest of the world.

