179
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:32,480
Along with sounding angry, German also has the reputation of having hilariously long words.

180
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,240
The reason for this is pretty simple.

181
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:38,720
A lot of the time, German words are just combinations of nouns stuck together.

182
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:42,320
In English, we usually cluster nouns together as modifiers,

183
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:48,240
like business computing solution, or online real-time cloud data management view,

184
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:51,520
or massively multiplayer online role-playing game.

185
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:55,360
But in German, there are never any spaces between the words in this structure.

186
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:59,920
