language has a whole word for it. A study by Boroditsky in 2011 looked at languages that

455
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:58,000
have gendered articles, like the ones I mentioned earlier. Spanish and German both have gendered

456
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:03,600
language, but the gender of objects varies. They asked speakers of each language to describe

457
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:07,920
various objects, and it turned out that they were more likely to talk about those objects

458
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:11,760
in ways that were consistent with the gendered article of their language.

459
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:15,520
So this shows that the gender system of a language might be connected with how the

460
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:20,880
