00:56:20,640 --> 00:56:21,360
Kiki Bubba

902
00:56:22,720 --> 00:56:26,480
If you've seen my video on the philosophy of color, you're already familiar with this.

903
00:56:26,480 --> 00:56:31,680
If I show you these two shapes, which one would you call Kiki, and which one would you call Bubba?

904
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:36,800
Strangely enough, almost everyone who has asked this question, no matter their cultural heritage

905
00:56:36,800 --> 00:56:41,760
or language, calls the spiky shape Kiki and the bulbous shape Bubba.

906
00:56:41,760 --> 00:56:46,960
Some languages seem to resist this effect, though, like Mandarin Chinese, Turkish, and Romanian.

907
00:56:46,960 --> 00:56:49,840
In these cases, there always seems to be a good reason, though.

908
00:56:49,840 --> 00:56:54,720
Romanian already has a word that sounds like Bubba, and it refers to a kind of sharp pain,

909
00:56:54,720 --> 00:56:57,200
which might remind them more of the spiky shape.

910
00:56:57,200 --> 00:57:02,560
Turkish has a word for babies and other cute things, so this might not fit quite right with the spiky shape.

911
00:57:02,560 --> 00:57:07,440
And in Mandarin Chinese, the syllables in Bubba and Kiki aren't really found in the language,

912
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:09,680
so both words might just sound weird.

913
00:57:09,680 --> 00:57:12,720
There are a few ideas for why this phenomenon might be happening.

914
00:57:12,720 --> 00:57:16,640
It could just be related to the way our mouths move when we say each word.

915
00:57:16,640 --> 00:57:21,600
When we say Bubba, our mouth is forced to be more rounded, whereas when we say Kiki,

916
00:57:21,600 --> 00:57:23,440
it's more angular and tight.

917
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:28,880
A more wild speculation has to do with the way we evolved and how sound tends to travel.

918
00:57:28,880 --> 00:57:32,080
If you're in a cave with a really smooth interior surface,

919
00:57:32,080 --> 00:57:34,480
sounds are probably more bassy and echo-y.

920
00:57:34,480 --> 00:57:37,760
If you're in a cave with a bunch of stalactites and rough surfaces,

921
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:40,400
sounds are probably a lot thinner and tinny.

922
00:57:40,400 --> 00:57:45,200
This kind of primordial association might be connected to the Bubba-Kiki thing.

923
00:57:45,200 --> 00:57:47,840
This phenomenon is really interesting for linguists,

924
00:57:47,840 --> 00:57:52,800
since it seems to show that the words we use for things are not entirely arbitrary.

925
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:56,640
